eniker die Bühne der Männlichkeiten. Dabei lassen sich diese Männlichkeitstypen an den Polen von Krise und Resouveränisierung ansiedeln, wie die literarischen und kulturellen Zeugnisse der Zeit zeigen.  aDandy, sportsman, décadent: Around 1900, new types of masculinity open up which share one thing - there is no longer the Man.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAllgemeine Literaturwissenschaft. 4aFin De Siècle. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aHomosexualität. 4aKrise. 4aKultur. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aMännlichkeit. 4aQueer Theory. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCrisis.  aCultural History.  aCulture.  aFin De Siècle.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aGeneral Literature Studies.  aHomosexuality.  aLiterary Studies.  aLiterature.  aMasculinity.  aQueer Theory.1 aHorlacher, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHülk, Walburga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIngenschay, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrämer, Lucia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKünkel, Britta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLickhardt, Maren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoloff, Volker, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRothstein, Anne-Berenike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchrader, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchuhen, Gregor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchuhen, Gregor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchwan, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.